commitResults.messageBody:
Without RunCommand, users have to rely on saving API endpoints then
running it by invoking the send command.

Let's add a run command that allows users to run API requests without
saving them.

This will improve user experience in terms of quickly testing out an
API.

More refactoring to the code is needed but due to big PRs soon to be
made by TJ and JX, I shall not make any potential breaking changes in
this commit in terms of code organisation.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor request related code
commitResults.messageBody:
Other than some minor typos, the request class and the subclasses seem
to repeat the creation of the instance attribute endpoint.

Let's remove the duplication and modify the abstract request constructor
to take in an endpoint and save the corresponding details for further
usage by child classes via getters.

This way new child request classes need not declare an endpoint
attribute within the class and clean up the call to get headers and data
as well.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add show command
commitResults.messageBody:
Without show command, users are unable to view the details of the endpoints saved.

Let's add a show command whereby users can specify the index to view the
particular endpoint on the display panel on the right.

Show command takes the form of: show 1.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor request related code
commitResults.messageBody:
Certain parts are duplicated and repeated for no clear purposes.

Let's fix some of the violations and improve code quality in terms of
extracting out smaller methods and make minor adjustments to how request
is executed.

This is so that further inheritance and reference to the request code
can reduce the amount of lines that are previously required but now
abstracted away.

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix display of endpoint and response
Add test for RunCommand & RunCommandParser
commitResults.messageBody:
Regression might occur without proper testing.

Let's add test cases for both RunCommand and RunCommandParser.

This will enforce functionality of RunCommand & RunCommandParser to be
in working condition.

commitResults.messageTitle: Refactor code for send & run command
Add show command details in user guide
Add quick run functionality
commitResults.messageBody:
Run command requires users to specify method and prefixes.

Let's add a way to quickly run a GET request to a specified url. The
command will look like this: "run https://google.com"

This will allow users to quickly test typical API endpoints.

commitResults.messageTitle: User guide update
Refactor based on Juliet's suggestion on LOD
Adjust ListCommand message
commitResults.messageBody:
ListCommand result is not helpful as it simply says all endpoints
listed. It does not account for the cases where there is no endpoints
saved.

Let's adjust the result output to prompt user to use show command if
there are endpoints saved, or use add command to add new endpoints.

This will make the result clearer to users.

I have also fixed the minor typos and clean up the numbering in
addCommand in order to allow users to easily copy paste the examples.
Some test cases are also fixed along the way.

Minor textual fix
Refactor CommandResult constructors
commitResults.messageBody:
Multiple constructors repeat the same logic of attribute assignment and
force various command classes to define boolean variables just for the
sake of creating a command result.

Let's make one main private constructor and respective factory
constructor for specialised command results.

This helps remove all boolean attributes when creating a command result.

While it may not be the best practice (Enum could be used), the setting
of boolean attributes are within commandResult and hence less likely to
result in mistaken boolean values.
